e league's modern history. The games were rescheduled to the back end of the season, pushing Super Bowl XXXVI into February 2002.","number":3},{"category":"legacy","header":"Apologized in 2017 for brain-injury claims handling","body":"During and after his 1989-2006 commissionership the NFL faced mounting evidence of traumatic brain injury among retired players — a crisis the league's response handled poorly. He issued a formal apology in 2017, and was elected to the Pro Football Hall of Fame's Centennial Class three years later.","number":4},{"category":"family","header":"Daughter Emily married into Rockefeller dynasty, 1990s","body":"His daughter Emily Elizabeth Tagliabue (b.1972) married John Davison 'Jamie' Rockefeller V — eldest son of Senator Jay Rockefeller IV. Three grandchildren followed, including a Laura Chandler named for Paul's wife Chandler Minter and a John Davison Rockefeller VI, the sixth to bear the name.","number":5}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"HD3289","display_label":"the Rockefeller who married his daughter Emily"}],"career":[{"role":"Lawyer","location":"Washington DC","start_year":1969,"end_year":1989,"notes":"Practiced law 1969-1989; later returned as Senior Counsel after NFL retirement.","organization":"Covington & Burling"},{"role":"Commissioner of the National Football League","location":"New York NY","start_year":1989,"end_year":2006,"notes":"5th NFL Commissioner. Took over from Pete Rozelle November 5, 1989. Expanded league from 28 to 32 teams (Charlotte/Carolina + Jacksonville added 1995, Baltimore Ravens 1996, Houston Texans 2002). Postponed games following 9/11. Moved Super Bowl XXVII away from Arizona for failure to recognize MLK state holiday. Established World League of American Football 1989. Retired Sept 1, 2006.","organization":"NFL"},{"role":"Senior Counsel","location":"Washington DC","start_year":2006,"notes":"Returned to law firm post-NFL.","organization":"Covington & Burling"},{"role":"Chairman, 